  RelyingPartyRegistrationConfig to build the SP registration without requiring
  a live Okta / Azure AD / Keycloak instance during development and CI.

  Key points:
  - entityID matches the value expected by Saml2LoginConfigTest.
  - SingleSignOnService points to localhost so redirect assertions work.
  - The X509Certificate below is a self-signed cert generated alongside the SP
    keystore. In a real deployment this would be the IdP's public signing cert.
-->
